    <item>
      <title><![CDATA[RubyTapas News: Free course, new hardware, and more]]></title>
      <link>https://rubytapas.dpdcart.com/subscriber/post?id=312</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<div class="blog-entry">
          <div class="blog-content"><h1>RubyTapas News</h1>
<p>Hi there! It's been a while since I did a news post. Here's what's new in the land of RubyTapas...</p>
<h2>Downtime</h2>
<p>First off, some of you may have had trouble getting your videos on Monday or Tuesday. This was because the service I use to distribute RubyTapas, DPD, was hit by a major distributed denial-of-service attack. They worked day and night with their datacenter to mitigate the attack and then to put measures in place to ensure that a DDoS can't bring the site down again in the future. You can <a href="http://us1.campaign-archive2.com/?u=5ed058f71d51b345f44b4fc6c&amp;id=2e63308f94">read their account of the even here</a>. Everything should be back to normal now.</p>
<h2>Extra Info in Receipts</h2>
<p>Several of you have asked if we could include more information on your RubyTapas receipts, such as tax IDs or your company's address. There is now an "Extra Info" field on your <a href="https://rubytapas.dpdcart.com/subscriber/profile">profile page</a>. You can use this field to add any extra info you want to be shown on your RubyTapas receipts.</p>
<p>An important note: this info will <em>not&nbsp;</em>be shown on the billing notifications you receive by email. However, those notifications will now contain a link to the full, printable receipt. If you follow this link you will find a receipt that contains the full details of the transaction.</p>
<h2>Free Code School course!</h2>
<p>All RubyTapas subscribers are invited to enroll for free in Code School's "Ruby Bits" course! If you love RubyTapas but feel link you're missing some foundational Ruby knowledge, this course is a fun way to fill in the blanks. Use this link to get in for free:&nbsp;<a href="http://mktg.codeschool.com/avdio875765/">http://mktg.codeschool.com/avdio875765/</a></p>
<h2>Downloading RubyTapas</h2>
<p>A number of industrious RubyTapas subscribers have written scripts to automate the process of batch-downloading the episode backlog. Here are scripts from:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/mislav/tapas-bar">Mislav&nbsp;MarohniÄ‡</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ebarendt/tapas">Eric Barendt</a></li>
<li><a href="https://gist.github.com/xpepper/5872399">Pietro Di Bello</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.benjaminfleischer.com/2013/04/03/mechanized-download/">Benjamin Fleischer</a></li>
</ul>
<div>Check 'em out!</div>
<h2>On the Road</h2>
<p>It's the home stretch of the 2013 conference season, and I for one am looking forward to spending a few months without packing a suitcase. However, those of you in Europe still have a few chances to come out and see me in the coming months. I'll be in Barcelona for <a href="http://www.baruco.org/">BaRuCo</a> next week, and then in Belgium for <a href="http://arrrrcamp.be/">Arrrrcamp</a> at the beginning of October. I look forward to meeting some of you there!</p>
<h2>New Mic</h2>
<p><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-FSjJe50L9pk/UiY-wyAmFMI/AAAAAAAB3tA/_EaluuKHN1c/w638-h479-no/20130903_152432.jpg" border="0" alt="Photo of my new microphone" width="400" height="300" /></p>
<p>This item's for the gearheads: this week I upgraded from my trusty <a href="http://bluemic.com/snowball/">Blue Snowball</a> microphone to a <a href="http://www.rodemic.com/mics/podcaster">Rode Podcaster</a> dynamic USB mic. I'm pretty thrilled about it; not only does it sound even better than the old mic, but a built-in monitor jack means I'm able to hear myself as the mic hears me in real-time. I also picked up a pair of <a href="http://thewirecutter.com/reviews/the-best-150-over-ear-headphones/">Sony MDR-7506 studio monitor headphones</a>, which are enabling me to be a lot more aware of the audio quality (or lack thereof) in my recordings. I'll be using these to tweak the sound quality as I make future episodes.</p>
<p>Listen for the new mic starting with episode 139.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Confident Ruby is done!</h2>
<p>My much-delayed book <a href="http://confidentruby.com">Confident Ruby is now finished</a>. If you haven't picked up a copy already, allow me to entice you with this 20% discount code, good for the next two weeks: CRTAPAS (Sorry, but I don't have a way to apply it to previous purchases)</p>
<h2>New TekPub Video</h2>
<p>Finally, if you just can't get enough video from me, TekPub has released a new hour and twenty minute screencast following a weekend web development project from beginning to initial release: <a href="http://tekpub.com/products/cowsays">The Making of Cowsays.com</a></p>
<p>That's all for now. Happy hacking!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>--</p>
<p>Avdi</p>
